Communicating (vague) threats via media is a way to blackmail someone with plausibly deniability. Consider that if Putin tried to blackmail Trump over, say, a "secret back channel" directly connecting the two, discovery of the backchannel would raise suspicion and spoil the blackmail scheme.

With that in mind, it's worth revisiting the previously mentioned Russian propaganda narrative accusing the Washington post of being a CIA front (with Jeff Bezos involved somehow). Trump has a habit of retweeting Russian fake news stories, and it looks like he actually believes some of them. In particular, it looks like he believes the one about U.S. intelligence agencies having a special relationship with the Washington Post:


